  "prompt": "I got placed in TCS's EIS stream in my campus placement. Will I get a job in EIS or in IT?",
  "response": "TCS's EIS (Enterprise Information Systems) is actually a part of their IT services. When you join TCS EIS, you will be working in an IT role, typically focusing on:\n\n1. Enterprise software implementation\n2. Business process consulting\n3. Technology integration\n4. ERP (Enterprise Resource Planning) solutions\n5. Digital transformation projects\n\nSo, you will be getting a job in IT, specifically in the Enterprise Information Systems domain. Your work will involve:\n- Working with enterprise-level software\n- Supporting digital transformation\n- Implementing technology solutions for businesses\n- Consulting on IT infrastructure and systems\n\nYour role might involve technologies like:\n- SAP\n- Oracle\n- Microsoft Dynamics\n- Cloud technologies\n- Integration platforms\n\nTypically, EIS professionals work on implementing and managing complex business systems across different industries like finance, manufacturing, healthcare, etc.\n\nThis is an IT job with a specific focus on enterprise-level solutions and digital transformation.",
